    blurbRight: `Residents currently living in Hunts Point have a median age of 32, an average household income of approximately $41,586, and roughly 12% of adults hold a bachelor's degree or higher. Historically a colonial estate for wealthy families, Hunts Point today maintains a prominent Dominican and Puerto Rican population, serving as a vibrant center for Latino culture and grassroots social activism.`,
